rails-template.title: Use .railsrc and template.rb to generate a new application

comments.body:
We're working on a shell script instead of generator/gems.

```
#!/bin/sh
APPNAME=$1

git clone --depth=1 https://github.com/pulibrary/rails-template $APPNAME
rm -rf !$/.git

sed -i.bak -e "s/rails_template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/.circleci/config.yml
rm $APPNAME/.circleci/config.yml.bak

sed -i.bak -e "s/drds-rails-template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/package.json
rm $APPNAME/package.json.bak

sed -i.bak -e "s/rails_template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/config/database.yml
rm $APPNAME/config/database.yml.bak

sed -i.bak -e "s/drds_rails_template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/config/environments/production.rb
rm $APPNAME/config/environments/production.rb.bak

sed -i.bak -e "s/drds-rails-template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/.lando.yml
rm $APPNAME/.lando.yml.bak

sed -i.bak -e "s/drds_rails_template/$APPNAME/g" $APPNAME/config/cable.yml
rm $APPNAME/config/cable.yml.bak

git init $APPNAME
```
What were the problems with the generator approach? It seemed really appealing not to have to keep updating this sample app.
